    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just a phase or hiding. it feels more fundamental than that. like the mechanism that makes me \"me\" has completely stalled. i'm just an object now. a physical object moving through space, eating and sleeping, but there's no one home. it feels like the essence is gone, and what's left is just... dead weight. why does the weight even need to stay here if the person is already gone?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
